article.headline: Saint Louis 66, Dayton 56
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Kevin Lisch scored 22 points and accounted for all but three of Saint Louis' final 17 points in a 66-56 victory over Dayton on Wednesday night. Tommie Liddell had 11 points and six assists and Ian Vouyoukas had 12 points and seven rebounds for the Billikens (17-10, 7-6 Atlantic-10), who won a matchup of conference teams with .500 records. Both of those players began Saint Louis' last game, a come-from-behind victory over LaSalle, on the bench, and Vouyoukas' double-figure game was only his second in the last seven. Charles Little had a career-high 23 points on 11-for-16 shooting and Brian Roberts 13 for Dayton (16-10, 6-7), which had won the previous three meetings in a series that's now tied at 18 games apiece. The Flyers were held to 38 percent shooting. A fastbreak layup with 6:08 left that put Saint Louis ahead 51-42 began a run of 12 straight points by Lisch, who was 4-for-6 from 3-point range and 8-for-8 from the line. He added a pair of 3-pointers and four free throws before Dwayne Polk hit a free throw for Saint Louis with 52 seconds to go. Vouyoukas added a pair of free throws in the final minute for Saint Louis, 13-for-15 at the free throw line. Saint Louis had a 14-0 run in the first half that transformed a seven-point deficit into a seven-point lead, capped by Luke Meyer's fastbreak layup off a behind-the-back pass from Lisch that made it 20-13 with 8:35 to go. Dayton went nearly seven minutes between points and trailed 32-24 at the break after another run by Saint Louis, this one 7-2. Dayton was without forward Monty Scott, who is scheduled to undergo season-ending knee surgery on Thursday. Little replaced Scott, who averages 10 points, in the lineup after coming off the bench the previous eight games. It was the 200th game in the Scottrade Center for Saint Louis, which is 144-56 at home since the arena opened in 1994.
